of amino acids and organic acids, respectively, in the colonization of cucumber roots by Ent. cloacae. The results reported here also indicate that catabolism of carbohydrates by this bacterium is more important than catabolism of amino acids and organic acids at lower population densities, despite the much higher relative quantities of amino acids and organic acids detected in cucumber root exudate.},
